<article>
    <h1>Track chief hits back</h1>
    <h2>Tang says leak of confidenti&#xAD;al in&#xAD;for&#xAD;ma&#xAD;tion will hin&#xAD;der work&#xAD;ings of ath&#xAD;let&#xAD;ics as&#xAD;so&#xAD;ci&#xAD;a&#xAD;tion</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200820/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-20"><time>2020-08-20</time></a>
        - <span>BRIEFING</span>
        - <span role="byline">Ni&#xAD;cole Chia cni&#xAD;cole@sph.com.sg</span>
    </section>

    <p>Sin­ga­pore Ath­let­ics pres­i­dent</p>
    <p>Tang Weng Fei has de­fended the pro­fes­sional in­de­pen­dence of the man­age­ment com­mit­tee after na­tional marathoner Soh Rui Yong (right) ques­tioned the as­so­ci­a­tion’s in­tegrity in a blog post last Satur­day.</p>
    <p>Sin­ga­pore Ath­let­ics (SA) has de­fended its man­age­ment com­mit­tee (MC) fol­low­ing com­ments about their pro­fes­sional in­tegrity by na­tional marathoner Soh Rui Yong in a blog post last Satur­day.</p>
    <p>The two-time SEA Games cham­pion made the re­marks in ref­er­ence to a le­gal is­sue in­volv­ing SA hon­orary sec­re­tary Eric Song, an as­so­ciate di­rec­tor at the Sin­ga­pore Man­age­ment Uni­ver­sity, over an al­leged defam­a­tory mes­sage sent via What­sApp and al­legedly leaked to ex­ter­nal par­ties, and an ex­tra­or­di­nary gen­eral meet­ing held last month.</p>
    <p>Re­spond­ing to queries from The Straits Times on Tues­day, SA pres­i­dent Tang Weng Fei stressed that the as­so­ci­a­tion is ac­count­able to its stake­hold­ers.</p>
    <p>He said: “It must be made very clear that there is no ex­trin­sic or po­lit­i­cal mo­ti­va­tion be­hind any de­ci­sions made by the SA man­age­ment.</p>
    <p>“The SA man­age­ment’s statu­tory obli­ga­tions are clear and bind­ing, and any ac­cu­sa­tions ques­tion­ing one’s pro­fes­sional in­de­pen­dence must be dealt with strictly.”</p>
    <p>He noted that SA is tak­ing le­gal ad­vice, “and will take the nec­es­sary ac­tion to en­sure that those who were re­spon­si­ble ac­count for their con­duct”.</p>
    <p>In March, SA, which gov­erns track and field, con­vened an in­de­pen­dent board of in­quiry to in­ves­ti­gate the source of the “leak of the con­tent from a pri­vate and confidenti­al What­sApp group chat among the man­age­ment”.</p>
    <p>Tang de­fended SA’s ap­proach with re­gard to the mat­ter, in­sist­ing: “The main is­sue at hand is that priv­i­leged, confidenti­al, and time-sen­si­tive in­for­ma­tion of SA is, once again, be­ing re­leased to ex­ter­nal par­ties.</p>
    <p>“There is an ex­ist­ing, ram­pant prac­tice of some MC mem­bers bring­ing dis­cus­sions and dis­agree­ments out of the MC meet­ing, which is presently be­ing re­vamped fun­da­men­tally.”</p>
    <p>He warned that “such prac­tices will only serve to hin­der the work­ings of SA as the ad­min­is­tra­tor of ath­let­ics in Sin­ga­pore”.</p>
    <p>“Man­age­ment de­ci­sions should be a re­sult of ro­bust and rig­or­ous de­bates, and in­for­ma­tion re­leased to the af­fil­i­ated mem­bers at the ap­pro­pri­ate time, not at the dis­cre­tion of ag­grieved par­ties,” he said.</p>
    <p>“Mem­bers of any NSA (na­tional sports as­so­ci­a­tion) man­age­ment should be af­forded the safe space to be able to dis­cuss their per­spec­tives, and bring their per­sonal ex­pe­ri­ences and ex­per­tise into the de­bates, with­out hav­ing the fear of their or­ganic opin­ions (be­ing) made public.”</p>
    <p>Tang em­pha­sised that the as­so­ci­a­tion would not com­ment on Song’s po­si­tion and course of ac­tion, but did not rule out as­sist­ing the lat­ter.</p>
    <p>He added: “While it is still not nec­es­sary or a sub­ject for dis­cus­sion at this point, it is pru­dent for SA to con­sider as­sist­ing Eric Song in his de­fence (or any other ac­tion), whether ad­min­is­tra­tively or oth­er­wise.”</p>
    <p>PRIV­I­LEGED IN­FOR­MA­TION</p>
    <p>Man­age­ment de­ci­sions should be a re­sult of ro­bust and rig­or­ous de­bates, and in­for­ma­tion re­leased to the af­fil­i­ated mem­bers at the ap­pro­pri­ate time, not at the dis­cre­tion of ag­grieved par­ties. ’’</p>
    <p>TANG WENG FEI, Sin­ga­pore Ath­let­ics pres­i­dent.</p>

